    ]
    ,
    
    "actions" : [
    
    
    
    "Avoid contact with hot parts or sources of ignition."
    ,
    
    
    "Use suction to remove ignitable vapours."
    ,
    
    
    "Attach warning sign in a clearly visible position."
    ,
    
    
    "Contain leaked media using non-flammable absorbent material and put it in a container designed for this purpose for disposal in accordance with local requirements."
    ,
    
    
    "Secure collection containers/vessels to prevent them from tipping over."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "warning"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "category" :
    
    
    "2Warnung"
    ,
    
    "source" :
    
    
    "Caustic fluids"
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "Danger of chemical burns"
    
    ]
    ,
    
    "actions" : [
    
    
    
    "Wear personal protective gear."
    ,
    
    
    "Ensure that there is good ventilation."
    ,
    
    
    "Avoid contact with caustic fluid."
    ,
    
    
    "If you do come into contact, wash off immediately with plenty of warm water and contact a doctor if necessary."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "warning"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "category" :
    
    
    "2Warnung"
    ,
    
    "source" :
    
    
    "Hot fuel and hot fuel lines."
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "Danger of scalding "
    
    ]
    ,
    
    "actions" : [
    
    
    
    "Allow the fuel to cool down before opening line connections."
    ,
    
    
    "Wear protective gloves. "
    ,
    
    
    "Wear protective goggles."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● The work area and tools must be cleaned before working on the injection system. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Thoroughly clean connection points and adjacent areas before loosening them using engine or brake cleaner and dry the cleaned area thoroughly. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● During disassembly work, close off all open connections immediately using suitable clean protection caps. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Do not remove the protection caps from any components until immediately before installation. Pack components to be used again in new, sealable plastic bags."
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Check the injection units and installation positions before installation by performing a visual inspection for damage and soiling. Check that the injection unit stem is clean. If necessary, clean the stem using a clean cloth, making sure not to damage it (no sharp tools!). "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● If the high-pressure lines will not be replaced, always mark the high-pressure lines during removal. The high-pressure lines must only be re-fitted on the same cylinder. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Make sure not to damage the injection unit when removing the old sealing ring. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Check all new O-rings for signs of damage before fitting them. Coat O-rings with assembly oil or engine oil before fitting them. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Align high-pressure lines without tension. Tighten all connections hand-tight at first and then tighten to the specified torque."
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● High-pressure lines must never be re-bent. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● A tool can only be used to loosen and tighten lines on the entire high-pressure system. All other assembly and disassembly processes must be carried out by hand and without tools. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Press fuel return hoses onto the injection units from above using your hand until they lock on each injection unit with an audible click (do not press in the release pin while doing this). Then press the release pin down. Check that the fuel return hoses are seated securely by pulling them upwards with your hand and check for leaks. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Individual common rail components cannot be disassembled. All the components must be replaced in the event of a fault. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● No assembly work must be carried out on the common rail system when the engine is running. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● The common rail system must not be bled by loosening high-pressure components after starting the engine. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Fit all tie-wraps, which you removed or cut during removal, back at the same position during installation. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● When the fuel system is open: Never use compressed air if at all possible. Do not move the vehicle if possible. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "● Also make sure that no diesel gets onto the coolant hoses. The hoses must be cleaned immediately if necessary. Always replace worn hoses."
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "To avoid letting the high-pressure pump run dry and to start the engine quickly after replacing parts, the following points must always be observed: "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "<b>Caution! Danger of irreparable damage to the high-pressure pump if it runs dry </b>"
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "◆ To avoid letting the fuel high-pressure pump run dry and to start the engine quickly after replacing parts, the following points must always be observed: "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "◆ If parts/components of the fuel system between the fuel tank and fuel high-pressure pump are removed or replaced, the basic setting must be performed in order to bleed the fuel system. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "◆ Perform initial fuel fill procedure after installing the high-pressure pump."
    
    }
    
    }
    
    ]
    
    }
    
    }
    